5-55:2.5 Profit Extraction In this section we review the truthful profit extraction mechanism ProfitExtractR .
5-56:This mechanism is a special case of a general cost sharing schema due to Moulin and Shenker [11] .
5-57:The goal of profit extraction is, given bids b, to extract a target value R of profit from some subset of the bidders .
5-58:ProfitExtractR: Given bids b, find the largest k such that the highest k bidders can equally share the cost of bidders can cover the cost, the mechanism has no winners .
5-59:Important properties of this auction are as follows: • ProfitExtractR is truthful .
5-60:• If R ≤ F(b), ProfitExtractR(b) = R; otherwise it has no winners and no revenue .
5-61:We will use this profit extraction mechanism in Section 5 with the following intuition .
5-62:Such a profit extractor makes it possible to treat this subset of bidders as a single bid with value F(S) .
5-63:Note that given a single bid, b, a truthful mechanism might offer it price t and if t ≤ b then the bidder wins and pays t; otherwise the bidder pays nothing (and loses) .
5-64:Likewise, a mechanism can offer the set of bidders S a target revenue R .
5-65:If R ≤ F(2) (S), then ProfitExtractR raises R from S; otherwise, the it raises no revenue from S. .
